<dl id="n03105d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03105d">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03105d"> 105(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Long Shot Winner</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The concluding air was &ldquo;Dixie,&rdquo; and as the exhilarating notes tumbled forth they were almost overpowered by the great clapping of hands from almost every table &hellip; This applause of the &ldquo;rebel&rdquo; air in a Northern city does puzzle a little; but it is not insolvable, The war with Spain, many years&apos; generous mint and water-melon crops, a few <mark>long-shot winners</mark> at the New Orleans race-track, and the brilliant banquets given by the Indiana and Kansas citizens who compose the North Carolina Society have made the South rather a &ldquo;fad&rdquo; in Manhattan. <small> O. Henry, <a name="OHFM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#OHFM"><cite title="source">The Four Million</cite></a> (1906) [&lsquo;A Cosmopolite in a Caf&eacute;&rsquo;] 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
